\Pi_1, \Pi_2
S
A, B, C, D, x_0, y_0, z_0\in \mathbb{R}
\mathcal{C}=\{(x,y,z)\in \mathbb{R}^3:(x-x_0)+(y-y_0)+(z-z_0)=R^2\}
\Pi_1=\{(x,y,z)\in \mathbb{R}^3:A(x-x_0)+B(y-y_0)+C(z-z_0)=D+R \wedge \ldots\}
\Pi_2=\{(x,y,z)\in \mathbb{R}^3:A(x-x_0)+B(y-y_0)+C(z-z_0)=D \wedge \ldots\}
S=\{(x,y,z)\in \mathbb{R}^3: (x,y,z)\in \mathcal{C} \wedge D\leq A(x-x_0)+B(y-y_0)+C(z-z_0)\leq D+R \wedge \ldots \}
